		</div>

		<!-- Begin Comments -->
		
		<b>Comment By mbartley, 2-18-09</b>
		<p>Sadly, it is not the first book shop to close in our town. The Stone Lion bookstore closed many years ago and whenever in old town, I still see the stone lion on the side of the building and mourn the loss of a great bookstore. How about an article on the great bookstores of the west. Bozeman, Moab, Boulder, Jackson are just a few of the towns with great bookstores that could be featured. These stores are important. I hope they can hang on in these hard tiimes.<br />
Also, I'd like to give a shout out to the Clark City Press for continuing to publish great literature and understanding that reading books is a tactile experience. I wear their hat with pride.<br />
Michael</p>
		
		<b>Comment By Jenny Shank, 2-19-09</b>
		<p>Thanks for the suggestion Michael.  Every once in a while I come across a great independent bookstore that still seems to be doing well, like Hamlet's Bookshoppe in Breckenridge.  It's in a Victorian house with a careful selection of books and a section on Western writers (at least they had this when I was there last year).  I've been to the bookstores in Moab and Boulder of course, but I'll have to make a trip to Bozeman and Jackson someday.</p>
		
